Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full #kettle{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.
> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%grams} and @British smoked bacon lardons{90%grams}. Fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the bacon has cooked, add the garlic to the pan and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @risotto rice{175%grams} to the bacon. Stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{15%grams} and @boiled water{600%ml}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Cook so there's no pink in the middle of the chicken. TIP: For hob cooking, pour in 800ml of boiled water a third at a time, stirring each time until the stock has been absorbed, 20-25 mins.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven, then stir in the @peas{120%grams} and @baby spinach{40%grams} until piping hot and wilted, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Mix the @pesto{32%grams}, @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams} and @butter{20%grams} into the risotto until melted and well combined.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

Share the chicken, bacon and pea risotto between your #bowls{}.

Drizzle over the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!